modify.help:	reminded as soon as someone submits a print request for this
modify.help:	form.
modify.help:	
modify.help:	[Frequency of alerts:]
modify.help:	You are expected to enter the number of minutes that should
modify.help:	elapse between repeated reminders. To keep you informed
modify.help:	that a form still needs to be mounted, the Line Printer Service
modify.help:	will keep issuing reminders until the form is mounted (or
modify.help:	enough print requests needing the form have been canceled or
modify.help:	changed to use a different form). Entering ONCE will mean you
modify.help:	want to reminded just once.
modify.help:	
modify.help:	[List the users who are denied access to this form:]
modify.help:	You are expected to list the users who are NOT allowed to
modify.help:	use this form. Please give the login names or user-ID's of the users,
modify.help:	not their proper names. Separate several names with commas.
modify.help:	
modify.help:	If you've already given a list of users, any names you give
modify.help:	now will be ADDED to the list; if you want to allow someone
modify.help:	who's already been denied, leave this field blank and enter their name
modify.help:	in the next. If it is easier to specify access
modify.help:	restrictions by listing just those who ARE allowed to use
modify.help:	the form, leave this field blank and fill in the next.
modify.help:	
modify.help:	You can deny EVERYBODY by entering the word "all."
modify.help:	
modify.help:	[List the only users who are allowed access to this form:]
modify.help:	You are expected to list the users who ARE allowed to use
modify.help:	this form. Please give the login names or user-ID's of the users, not
modify.help:	their proper names. Separate several names with commas.
modify.help:	
modify.help:	If you've already given a list of users, any names you give
modify.help:	now will be ADDED to the list. You can allow EVERYBODY by
modify.help:	entering the word "all."
remove.help:ABSTRACT:
remove.help:	[GENERAL]
remove.help:	You use the "remove" task to remove a form from the print
remove.help:	service. No more print requests will be accepted for it
remove.help:	and the form definition will be destroyed. Any print
remove.help:	requests currently queued to print on this form will be
remove.help:	CANCELED.
remove.help:	
remove.help:	
remove.help:	[Enter the names of the forms to remove:]
remove.help:	You are expected to enter the name of the form you want to
remove.help:	remove. You can give a list of forms to remove by
remove.help:	separating the names with commas. If you don't
remove.help:	know a form name, press CHOICES, to get a list of known forms.
remove.help:	
remove.help:	NOTE
remove.help:	If any print requests are currently queued to print on the form(s), you will
remove.help:	not be able to remove them.
status.help:ABSTRACT:
status.help:	[GENERAL]
status.help:	You use the "forms" task to get a
status.help:	list of all forms you have defined in the print service.
status.help:	The report will include an indication of which printers the
status.help:	forms are currently mounted on.
